The paper presents a deep learning-based approach for segmenting corneal tissue interfaces in OCT images. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are a popular deep learning technique, indicating that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves extensive validation of the approach, which could suggest that it belongs to the Measurement (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
